shingle short, a
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:take a shingle off
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka a shingle off, a shingle loose.  1953 16 M A33 Thames DHS 2 SHINGLE SHORT (with variations) `a screw loose' perhaps deriving from <i>have a tile loose</i>, with shingle a metaphor for head or hair (cf thatch); or from be a bit short, missing on top; to be not all there (on top)
