Author: LYTTELTON
Vol / Page: 34
Edition:
Quote: Mr. Acland used an odd colonial phrase for a half-witted person: `shingle-short'. Wooden shingles being used, like the wooden church-spires in Kent and Sussex, for house-roofs, it means, weak in the head.
